mentalist</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 4:58:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Question for DKP guilds</span><hr size=1> Recently my guild transitioned from a mostly exp/casual raiding atmosphere to the exact opposite. Using the Stormhammer Tier system as a reference point, in the past two months we've shot from a Tier 1 guild into a borderline Tier 4 guild. <br>
<br>
Consequently, to go along with our new Raid mentality, we've revised our loot system to a DKPish one. In essence, Raids=points=items. Right now the Officers and Raid leaders are trying to come up with a good list of item point values before we go into our final phase of transitioning to this new system. Tonight, I butted heads with my Guild Leader over the Bile Drenched Robe:<br>
<br>
Bile Drenched Flesh Robe <br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP <br>
AC: +50 Wis: +20 Int: +20 Magic Resist: +10 Fire Resist: +10 Cold Resist: +10 Poison Resist: +10 Disease Resist: +10 Mana: +80 <br>
Weight: 2.0 <br>
Classes: Wizard Magician Enchanter Necromancer <br>
Races: Human High Elf Erudite Dark Elf Gnome Iksar <br>
Inventory Slot: Chest <br>
Required: Yes <br>
Can be stored in Medium and larger containers <br>
Effect: Flowing Thought V <br>
Type: Triggered <br>
Charges: Unlimited <br>
<br>
Now, our average intake of points per player, per week, is about 5-6. My guild leader is saying that the above item should be worth about 38 points. I say it should be worth about 27. He's saying it should cost a lot because of how friggin awesome it is. I'm saying it should cost a lot, but not so much that it would take upwards of two months for our average member to recoup the cost.<br>
<br>
So here's my question to anyone in a DKP guild: Should we deliberately price certain items high in order to reward those who raid so much that they can afford them? Or should we choose a middle ground, that doesn't alienate our average members, but still makes the item cost enough to be an achievement? <br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
 <p>- Ignitz Gemcaller<br>
60th Arch Mage of Requiem</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 661<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 6:32:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for DKP guilds</span><hr size=1> Are your people allowed to bid their points?<br>
