 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaniel>Zaniel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 11:54:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Robes</span><hr size=1> Whatever you do ... please ... don't set points values on items. Just set points on the raid mobs and then let members bid in an open market on items.<br>
<br>
Our guild uses a bidding based DKP system and we have ZERO loot issues. Bidding allows points to be flushed from the system. Hardcore players accumulate large numbers of points and compete with one another for the top items. Casual players buy lots of good mid range items that the top players don't want for low points values.<br>
<br>
Bidding ensures that hardcore players don't simply buy all those little one point items for their twinks. It also prevents new recruits from outspending an old member unless that older member has already burnt all their points.<br>
<br>
We have a number of various rules to cover special items and unusual circumstances but on the whole we let it flow freely. If you're not prepared to bid high on a item well then perhaps you didnt want it as badly as that other member who is bidding high on an item that he obviously sees as a worthwhile upgrade.<br>
<br>
We have a minimum points value which is fluid per encounter. Its based on number of people required for encounter and how many classes can use it, its calculated on the fly for every mob and each item.<br>
<br>
Our system also slowly reduces the points values of various mobs as they become easier and require less people. Its to make us push further and harder. For example Arch Lich started out as 4 points, he's down to 3 and approaching 2 as we do him with less and less people. This prevents bottom-farming.<br>
<br>
Points per item also needs to be recalibrated regularly to account for inflation. A bidding system reduces strain on the officers substantially because items have no value to be decided. <p>Zaniel Stormseeker<br>
65th Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moontaylesilverleaf>Moontayle Silverleaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 1:29:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Robes</span><hr size=1> We're basically setting a minimum bid cost for items, and then allowing people to bid up to twice that. Top two point holders who bid for it then roll as long as they are within 5 points of each other. Otherwise the person with the most points gets it.<br>
<br>
