- Gwinie Gemcaller, 57th Druid of Requiem</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aquaminismallwater>Aquamini Smallwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 2:53:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Robes</span><hr size=1> I have this robe its very nice item and i dont see myself changing anytime soon. cost was 98 DKP. it might seem like a lot but my guild does like 4 raids a day.<br>
<br>
Aquamini Smallwater 64 MAGE <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aquaminismallwater>Aquamini Smallwater</A> at: 12/18/02 3:11:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arciuskarn>Arcius Karn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 7:06:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Robes</span><hr size=1> DKP Spent = DKP Given, give the items a value before deciding on how much to give for the raid.<br>
<br>
Let's say you kill the Blood of Ssrazheza when going after Emp. If there are 50 people on the raid and a belt drops (we'll say 18 dkp) and an earring (12 dkp) then 30 dkp is spent. Blood of Ssrazheza kills should give ~0.6 dkp everytime (0.6 x 50 = 30). If a little less is spent for bad drops, or a bit more is spent for great drops, it averages out.<br>
<br>
This way people aren't spending too many points and they aren't spending far too little, either. My guild tried dkp for awhile and this seemed like the best way to do it, but I could be wrong =p<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalamos>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 454<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 8:40:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Robes</span><hr size=1> My guild uses a DKP system and separates loot into 3 tiers.  This Robe is considered a tier 3 item at the moment.  We're currently at the level of clearing Ssra bosses minus the Emp and Blood.  Our system follows a method similar to what Arcius stated ... DKP IN = DKP OUT on average (hopefully).<br>
<br>
For example, the Burrower Parasite is worth 1 DKP in our system.  The Robe costs 25 DKP.  Say we had 50 people on a Burrower kill.  Then 50 DKP would be earned.  A Bile Drenched Flesh Robe (-25.00 DKP), a Ring of Living Ore (-8.00 DKP) and a Shard from Unfathomable Depths (-15.00 DKP) were the drops.  So 50 DKP was earned and 48 DKP was spent.<br>
<br>
Sometimes more DKP is earned then spent, and sometimes it's the other way around.  Over time it tends to average out.<br>
<br>
I guess the cost of the Robe should depend on what level of bosses your guild is killing and the cost of other available Robes.  I know that once we start killing the Emp and move on to VT the cost of this Robe will drop.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.san.rr.com/thegreenmile/kalamos-1hz.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24305">My Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ~ <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.forgedsouls.org">Forged Souls</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1252<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 8:49:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1131.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Robes</span><hr size=1> The problem with bidding is that it can create contention among guildmates through jealousy...  it's sorta cold, you know?  I mean these are your brothers, and youre competing against them now.<br>
<br>
No system is perfect, for sure, but I would say that robe should have a high point value.  Its basically what most casters would consider the best possible robe before emperor quality, which is a long way off.  To top it all off, that robe is RARE.  It really doesnt drop much anymore.<br>
<br>
